**Description**

There is an issue reading data from the spreadsheet. All cells are somehow converted to numbers even if they contain text. For example the word "testing" becomes 11. I have used the same code with other excel files but text is returned where appropriate. 

**Information**

.Net Framework 4.7.2
[OpenXmlReadProblem.zip](https://github.com/OfficeDev/Open-XML-SDK/files/2723115/OpenXmlReadProblem.zip)

**Repro**

Please see the attached windows form application. The Excel file is in the bin path (Deposits.xlsx)

```
            using (SpreadsheetDocument spreadsheetDocument =
            SpreadsheetDocument.Open(Path.Combine(Application.StartupPath, "Deposits.xlsx"), false))
            {

                //open the worksheet
                WorkbookPart workbookPart = spreadsheetDocument.WorkbookPart;
                WorksheetPart worksheetPart = GetWorksheetPart(workbookPart, "Deposits");
                SheetData sheetData = worksheetPart.Worksheet.Elements<SheetData>().First();

                string text;
                foreach (Row r in sheetData.Elements<Row>())
                {
                    if (r.RowIndex != 1) //skip first row
                    {
                        Debug.WriteLine($"Row: {r.RowIndex}");
                        foreach (Cell c in r.Elements<Cell>())
                        {
                            text = c.CellValue.Text;
                            Debug.WriteLine($"Cell {c.CellReference}: {text}");
                        }
                    }
                }
            }

        public WorksheetPart GetWorksheetPart(WorkbookPart workbookPart, string sheetName)
        {
            string relId = workbookPart.Workbook.Descendants<Sheet>().First(s => sheetName.Equals(s.Name)).Id;
            return (WorksheetPart)workbookPart.GetPartById(relId);
        }

```

